deck: Letterer. Christy letters comics & does assorted art stuff in San Francisco. She believes this to be some sort of inception dream and expects to wake up in NYC any minute. She exists primarily on a diet of greens, gluten-free Oreo-like cookies and pizza. Known to change hair colors at random, Christy is adept at blending into her urban environment to avoid her natural enemy - the sun.
name: Christy Sawyer

description: Doug Garbark is a comic book colorist out of Pittsburgh, PA that has worked with such publishers as DC Comics, Vertigo, Image Comics, IDW Publishing, Boom Studios, Lucha Underground, Black Mask Studios, 215 Ink, and various independent publishers. Some of his notable works include DC Bombshells, Vertigo Quarterly: SFX, Hitman Agent 47, Last Sons of America, Prophet, and the Eisner nominated In The Dark horror anthology.
name: Doug Garbark

deck: Japanese stage, TV and film actor known for his roles in Batman Begins, The Last Samurai, Inception and Godzilla.
description: Ken Watanabe was born in Japan in 1959. Achieving success in show business both domestically as well as internationally, he has won the Japan Academy Prize for Best Actor twice, and has been nominated for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actor once. In Hollywood, he is known for his roles in Memoirs of a Geisha, The Last Samurai and Inception among other films. To comic book reading audiences, he is known for his role as the decoy Ra's al Ghul in Christopher Nolan's Batman Begins.
name: Ken Watanabe
